  "body": "**üßê Motivation**\r\nI am currently using OpenZepplin contracts in my Brownie based project. Even though the code I have written is fully unit tested, when I run `brownie test -C` I get 0% coverage for all of the OpenZepplin files, thus the overall coverage report reports a very low % for my project. I was going to add tests targetting OpenZepplin myself but figured it might be something that is useful for the community and could be integrated into this repo, opposed to just my personal repo. \r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\n- Pytest / Brownie tests for OpenZepplin Contracts\r\n- I can assist with this and/or submit a PR if that is of interest.\r\n\r\nThoughts from an OpenZepplin engineer would be awesome.\r\n\r\nCheers,\r\nJustin\r\n\r\n<!-- Make sure that you have reviewed the OpenZeppelin Contracts Contributor Guidelines. -->\r\n<!-- https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md -->\r\n",
