    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Hello @justinpezzack \r\n\r\nBrownie is not part of our work process when building and testing our contract. We currently use hardhat (with various modules) to test everything. Also, as discussed in previous issues, we do not consider the test scripts to be part of the deliverables. Users are free to reuse them to further test their projects, but we do not take any specific actions to make sure that our test scripts work outside this repo.\r\n\r\nI'm not exactly sure what the demand for brownie tests covering our contract is, but I would personally not feel comfortable shipping this considering it is not the goal of this repo to prove such tests AND we are not familiar with brownie. \r\n\r\nIf you think this would be valuable, then maybe a community-managed repo would make more sense. ",
